    "body": "### Problem\n\nInvoking the difftool plugin via git difftool always prints the following message: \"Already only one window\"\nPerhaps there is an unnecessary call to `:only`  in the implementation?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ngit config:\n```ini\n[difftool \"nvimdiff-clean\"]\n\tcmd = nvim --clean \\\n\t\t-c 'packadd nvim.difftool' \\\n\t\t-c \\\"DiffTool $LOCAL $REMOTE\\\" \\\n```\n\nin a git directory with modified files do\n```\ngit difftool -d -t nvimdiff-clean\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo unnecessary messages printed when difftool is executed\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\ncommit 0ed5e00077dcc8ab1a99dd76a85628b11504ffa4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim doesn't have difftool\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
